"attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Jose, Pedro, Domingo, Roberto, Carlos, Ricardo, Albertino, Alejandro, Almario, Altagracia, Andres, Armando.  Portuguese Ilidio.  Italian Antonio, Gennaro, Anastasio, Federico, Marco, Quirino.","Italian; Portuguese (<b>Basílio</b>): from the personal name <i>Basilio</i>, <i>Basílio</i>, from Latin <i>Basilius</i> (see   Basil  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Basil","meanings":["From the Greek name <i>Basileios</i> ‘royal’ (a derivative of <i>basileus</i> ‘king’). This name was borne by  St Basil  the Great (  <i>c.</i>330–379 ), bishop of Caesarea, a theologian regarded as one of the Fathers of the Eastern Church. It was also the name of several early saints martyred in the East."]},{"name":"Bacilio","meanings":["Hispanic (mainly Mexico and Peru): variant spelling of   Basilio  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Basilia was born in 1110, in Fougères, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France. She married Jean II de Dol, Seigneur de Dol in 1131, in Fougères, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France. They were the parents of at least 3 daughters. She died in 1145, in Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France, at the age of 35."},"et":{"1110–1145":"1110–1145","1115–1162":"1115–1162","1132–Female":"1132–Surnud","1135–Female":"1135–Surnud","1140–1197":"1140–1197","about 1140":"umbes 1140","1115":"1115","1135":"1135","1145":"1145","1110":"1110","1132":"1132","1131":"1131","1197":"1197","1140":"1140","1162":"1162","Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Brittany, France":"Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Fougères, Fougères-Vitré, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Fougères, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Fougères, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Fougères, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, France":"Dol-de-Bretagne, Ille-et-Vilaine, Bretagne, Prantsusmaa","Dol-de-Bretagne, Saint-Malo,